🚨 <b>Boletim de Cyber Segurança - Técnica</b><br><br><b>Visão geral:</b><br>• 0 com severidade Crítica<br>• 3 com severidade Alta<br>• 2 novas CVEs<br>• 0 novos advisories/exploits<br><span style="color:#b6bcc6;">────────────────────────────────────</span><br><span style="color:#5b8def;"><b>Infraestrutura</b></span> - Docker / ESX / Elastic / VMware<br><br>📰 <b>NanoClaw integrates with Docker to bring trust to AI agents - Techzine Global</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#2563eb;"><b>Docker</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>NanoClaw integrates with Docker to bring trust to AI agents. Consulte o link para mais informações.<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMipgFBVV95cUxOaEg1RGJrZWtiTVlSbk5JZnlRd2xVV2tEVjBHODI1cW1SQUFDdFVzSE5VQUkxcE55OGFqTEZNM3VXUFRHRFg3VzVXWUk2MWlaRjhDaERUamVYclhyTVdPSVJKeF9Cb2FFcG95dnlyeUhNSU9OV1RNZ19CbGpkUVdpMGxLOTZfT0FudXplbU9PVGJLUUgwbjNjYXhMTl93YTlqc21DRTd3?oc=5<br>📰 <b>Achieving Test Reliability for Native E2E Testing: Beyond Fixing Broken Tests</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#eab308;"><b>Média</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#2563eb;"><b>Docker</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> https://www.docker.com/blog/feed/<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>End-to-end (E2E) tests are particularly important for native applications that run on various platforms (Android/iOS), screen sizes, and OS versions. E2E testing picks up differences in behavior across this fragmented ecosystem. But keeping E2E tests reliable is often more challenging than writing them in the first place. The fragmented device ecosystem, gaps in test frameworks,...<br><b>Link:</b> https://www.docker.com/blog/native-e2e-test-reliability/<br>📰 <b>O NanoClaw está na sua sandbox do Docker agora – isso pode impedir que os agentes de IA fiquem descontrolados? - qstage.com.br</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#2563eb;"><b>Docker</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>O NanoClaw está na sua sandbox do Docker agora – isso pode impedir que os agentes de IA fiquem descontrolados?<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.?oc=5<br>📰 <b>How to Run Claude Code with Docker: Local Models, MCP Servers, and Secure Sandboxes</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#2563eb;"><b>Docker</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> https://www.docker.com/blog/feed/<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>Claude Code is quickly becoming a go-to AI coding assistant for developers and increasingly for non-developers who want to build with code. But to truly unlock its potential, it needs the right local infrastructure, tool access, and security boundaries. In this blog, we’ll show you how to run Claude Code with Docker to gain full...<br><b>Link:</b> https://www.docker.com/blog/run-claude-code-with-docker/<br>📰 <b>Secure Agent Execution with NanoClaw and Docker Sandboxes</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#2563eb;"><b>Docker</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> https://www.docker.com/blog/feed/<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>Agents have enormous potential to power secure, personal AI assistants that automate complex tasks and workflows. Realizing that potential, however, requires strong isolation, a codebase that teams can easily inspect and understand, and clear control boundaries they can trust. Today, NanoClaw, a lightweight agent framework, is integrating with Docker Sandboxes to deliver secure-by-design agent execution....<br><b>Link:</b> https://www.docker.com/blog/nanoclaw-docker-sandboxes-agent-security/<br>📰 <b>NanoClaw and Docker partner to make sandboxes the safest way for enterprises to deploy AI agents - Venturebeat</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#2563eb;"><b>Docker</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>NanoClaw and Docker partner to make sandboxes the safest way for enterprises to deploy AI agents<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMitgFBVV95cUxPZ0VoeENqLWdjdDFnT0wtOGtVM2NFRzU4eUh3M2RITE1ZRU9GUnhvZUJTNjQxV1JfMW5xVDRYMHR0b2ZZSEZLMXlGZkEzamNQU3F4Wk5odzYtSkRiS2lMRGlYb3FmTkVXODJiY01IQkJvQzJDdnVNVjhwYVBXNkJwbGRyVVN0bmJ2V3BjbDdGSjZoTFZxTFBLLTR3b1VtZ21wZzVEaGd6cG9SZHVQVHYxWlQ0djRkdw?oc=5<br>📰 <b>NanoClaw latches onto Docker Sandboxes for safer AI agents - theregister.com</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#2563eb;"><b>Docker</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>NanoClaw latches onto Docker Sandboxes for safer AI agents. Consulte o link para mais informações.<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMihAFBVV95cUxQV3lZTWVwekNFREJmbW1OeXRFVXU3YTRqaTc0YVQ2aE9pTDVmdFZZbEoxZ2lwd0RhOGJUSWQ4ZkFHTVBMUjFneDVranJEVkdfTnQteG5GU2RNZmY0eW5DcGRQamtaRnhqMkIzeUx3YklDQnlYdmx1eEoxUlY2bGZGYTlyS2s?oc=5<br>📰 <b>Announcing the 2026 vExpert Program</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#0ea5e9;"><b>VMware</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> https://blogs.vmware.com/feed<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>Tweet Congratulations to our New and Returning vExperts Last week we officially kicked off the 2026 vExpert Program and Broadcom would like to say congratulations to the new and returning vExperts. Thank you for your continued leadership and contribution to the VMware community. The vExpert Program continues to grow because of individuals who consistently share …<br><b>Link:</b> https://blogs.vmware.com/vexpert/2026/03/12/announcing-the-2026-vexpert-program/<br>📰 <b>Announcing the 2026 vExpert Program</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#0284c7;"><b>ESX</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> https://blogs.vmware.com/feed<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>Tweet Congratulations to our New and Returning vExperts Last week we officially kicked off the 2026 vExpert Program and Broadcom would like to say congratulations to the new and returning vExperts. Thank you for your continued leadership and contribution to the VMware community. The vExpert Program continues to grow because of individuals who consistently share …<br><b>Link:</b> https://blogs.vmware.com/vexpert/2026/03/12/announcing-the-2026-vexpert-program/<br>🚨 <b>CVE-2026-1527 - Elastic</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#eab308;"><b>Média</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#f59e0b;"><b>Elastic</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> NVD<br><b>CVSS:</b> 4.6<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>ImpactWhen an application passes user-controlled input to the upgrade option of client.request(), an attacker can inject CRLF sequences (
) to: * Inject arbitrary HTTP headers * Terminate the HTTP request prematurely and smuggle raw data to non-HTTP services (Redis, Memcached, Elasticsearch) The vulnerability exists because undici writes the upgrade value directly to the socket without validating for invalid header characters: // lib/dispatcher/client-h1.js:1121 if (upgrade) { header += `connection: upgrade
upgrade: ${upgrade}
` }<br><b>Link:</b> https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-1527<br><span style="color:#b6bcc6;">────────────────────────────────────</span><br><span style="color:#ec008c;"><b>Segurança</b></span> - Check Point / Qualys / SentinelOne<br><br>📰 <b>SentinelOne Down 4%, Then Up 3%: Can $1B Revenue Milestone Quell Skepticism? - 24/7 Wall St.</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#9333ea;"><b>SentinelOne</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>SentinelOne Down 4%, Then Up 3%: Can $1B Revenue Milestone Quell Skepticism?. Consulte o link para mais informações.<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMitAFBVV95cUxOSnlkV3J2SERPbk9ZY0NWYi0xNk1HaGgtZGRHVTQtSE85djRlSnBGYkdOQ3VNZVQ1X1lKRHdmZE9rRksybGZiMUxUbzA3am41RXRGam5MbDhmMnpIaXEzd1JDakNCeE9FNWZreVlZZUtHVUhiZWJTZThKVldVMGk3WHNveUFMQUx2WjhHS0JaMmRjZHJ3T2JoMDNmUUVOMGt0Smd5Rk9SenVmWHk1WGRpUmxRZWY?oc=5<br>📰 <b>SentinelOne CEO: Microsoft has more vulnerabilities than any other company - 24/7 Wall St.</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#9333ea;"><b>SentinelOne</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>SentinelOne CEO: Microsoft has more vulnerabilities than any other company. Consulte o link para mais informações.<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiuAFBVV95cUxNS0ZMT1ZhRlZ5Yk1wZng0MHpyaXhEWWdMRE5CdV9VVVo3T2xSZUNkeTVTOE1ZZ3NvdnZsdUkydUNOaFk1V0tUV1phNGExcEtTLTVjRTZ5Z3hiX2tXY0FVdnZQaGVvWmJTejJMN2Nkd1dBaVo2TE1OYkh2U0lYUUdIYUxnajBsdC1KeENBUWpDNXhmdklwV200TWNUOC1iYmRQT1NJWWRTdmZ1UnlOS2I1aEdmWmh5VWdX?oc=5<br>📰 <b>Nine CrackArmor Flaws in Linux AppArmor Enable Root Escalation, Bypass Container Isolation - The Hacker News</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#7c3aed;"><b>Qualys</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>Nine CrackArmor Flaws in Linux AppArmor Enable Root Escalation, Bypass Container Isolation<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMihAFBVV95cUxQdmM0d3AxWGNKbVZzTGFfcDBXM0sxaW5NUWl2V2xQWlhncUFaMWg0YUZ5QnhoTmNCdGR1Rl85bThrTnVJUGVNTjVjWkpVMlhDcHVnVWc1WkE3NzdMWEZyeVktbDR2MXYwU0x3RVZUdDNKNjdidHhzSVI2SjBybnBwSGRwZTM?oc=5<br>📰 <b>CrackArmor: Critical AppArmor Flaws Enable Local Privilege Escalation to Root - Qualys</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#dc2626;"><b>Alta</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#7c3aed;"><b>Qualys</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>CrackArmor: Critical AppArmor Flaws Enable Local Privilege Escalation to Root. Consulte o link para mais informações.<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.?oc=5<br>📰 <b>SentinelOne Reaches $1b Revenue As Profitability Shifts Risk Reward View - simplywall.st</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#9333ea;"><b>SentinelOne</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>SentinelOne Reaches $1b Revenue As Profitability Shifts Risk Reward View. Consulte o link para mais informações.<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.?oc=5<br>📰 <b>Is Check Point (CHKP) Using Its New AI Governance Service To Redefine Its Cyber Moat? - simplywall.st</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#ef4444;"><b>Check Point</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>Is Check Point (CHKP) Using Its New AI Governance Service To Redefine Its Cyber Moat?. Consulte o link para mais informações.<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.?oc=5<br>📰 <b>SentinelOne Q4 Earnings Call Highlights - MarketBeat</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#dc2626;"><b>Alta</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#9333ea;"><b>SentinelOne</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>Consulte o link para mais informações.<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMimAFBVV95cUxPMmU4eGlpbDRpZ0p5RFR1UGFzZDNiazFyOXZhbE94bmRWX3JMdWR2RXR2enZHZnVNQUs2ZG5oOTMyTzZtYmFDSHhRbXhUaXpJU0lTellmSFZpV2M4bmxuMzVQQkxsRGF6R09LTTEyQ2ZSYWY1OTJrN0RPTnBZdmQ3VWVxei1ieHFLUFBUS3E1cTNhRDlIQnZhUg?oc=5<br>📰 <b>SentinelOne Partners ‘Rapidly Expanding Beyond The Endpoint’: CEO Tomer Weingarten - crn.com</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#9333ea;"><b>SentinelOne</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>SentinelOne Partners ‘Rapidly Expanding Beyond The Endpoint’: CEO Tomer Weingarten. Consulte o link para mais informações.<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMiugFBVV95cUxQY2dZa0wyekhzaTNnbVg5Ujl4QnVXZkVHTGRfUEhNdlJIbWRZcXlTNjZCc2lLNGw0ajhGVE9qVmtTU0pOQnNLTi1ua3Z3NjhzQ2xmQjQ0X3otRjYzU0JIV1lIVXZPTXlPVXEzdWk1LUhVM2x1b2ZlQnhST3A3dEVsOEpLUzgxenViQTVFaTBKY050NUZmZkQ2cTlqc3JWUlotWXh2VmtjWGoySm9tSEFaMUtaX1p6LVFyMUE?oc=5<br>📰 <b>SentinelOne Projects Lower Q1 Profit Amid Competitive Pressure | 2026 - News and Statistics - IndexBox - Market Intelligence Platform</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#9333ea;"><b>SentinelOne</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>SentinelOne Projects Lower Q1 Profit Amid Competitive Pressure | 2026 - News and Statistics<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.com/rss/articles/CBMimAFBVV95cUxOOVUyQ1BVb1lyTjBWeDR4TjdpZk1FU081ejVJd3ktMUJmQ3I1R0ktbU5uMVF2QVRGM2lRVTBva1BmUFUwVzlLZTlvc0hDdEQwTnFkSlRDTHZxOXZ6OTYwQzd4dEd4MmZCeVlGWjB4WWdMN2g1MXVLSVBQRTB6Q3dreWV6aWFIY1ZTZG1JektxNXdDeF9JLU9lTg?oc=5<br>🚨 <b>CVE-2026-32249 - Check Point</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#eab308;"><b>Média</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#ef4444;"><b>Check Point</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> NVD<br><b>CVSS:</b> 5.3<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>Vim is an open source, command line text editor. From 9.1.0011 to before 9.2.0137, Vim&#x27;s NFA regex compiler, when encountering a collection containing a combining character as the endpoint of a character range (e.g. [0-0ֻ]), incorrectly emits the composing bytes of that character as separate NFA states. This corrupts the NFA postfix stack, resulting in NFA_START_COLL having a NULL out1 pointer. When nfa_max_width() subsequently traverses the compiled NFA to estimate match width for the look-behind assertion, it dereferences state-&gt;out1-&gt;out without a NULL check, causing a segmentation fault. This vulnerability is fixed in 9.2.0137.<br><b>Link:</b> https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-32249<br><span style="color:#b6bcc6;">────────────────────────────────────</span><br><span style="color:#5fa88b;"><b>Sistemas / Cloud</b></span> - Azure / Office / Ubuntu / Windows Server / WordPress<br><br>📰 <b>Every word Igor Tudor said with full X-rated speech, Romero update and &#x27;beautiful&#x27; Spurs player - Football London</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#eab308;"><b>Média</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#dc2626;"><b>Office</b></span><br><b>Fonte:</b> Google News RSS<br><b>CVSS:</b> N/D<br><b>Resumo:</b><br>Every word Igor Tudor said with full X-rated speech, Romero update and &#x27;beautiful&#x27; Spurs player<br><b>Link:</b> https://news.google.?oc=5<br>📰 <b>We’re talking 1,000 private security guards, LAPD SWAT teams, bomb-sniffing dogs, and a fleet of surveillance drones circling overhead... Read: dw.news/k4jfcvcm - facebook.com</b><br><br><b>Criticidade:</b> <span style="color:#16a34a;"><b>Baixa</b></span><br><b>Ferramenta:</b> <span style="color:#dc2626;"><b>Office